      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a loud humming noise but the fan isnt actually spinning. any idea what's wrong and is it safe to go look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A loud humming sound without the fan spinning usually indicates that the motor is receiving power but the fan blades are likely obstructed, seized, or the capacitor has failed to provide the necessary torque to start the motor. It is generally safe to approach the unit if you are wearing appropriate protective gear like gloves and safety glasses, but you should never touch the electrical components or attempt to force the fan blades. You should turn off the breaker to the unit immediately to prevent any potential electrical hazards before inspecting the area. The best course of action is to call a professional HVAC technician, as they have the tools to diagnose the specific cause, such as a clogged condenser coil, a damaged capacitor, or a motor bearing issue.",
