    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i'm just a bit confused why it would hum like that if nothing is physically blocking it. it's such a weird, glitchy sound. is there anything else that can cause that kind of intermittent electrical buzzing without a visible break in the parts?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That \"glitchy\" buzzing often comes from components failing to hold the magnetic field correctly, such as a worn-out capacitor that can't provide enough starting power, or a dirty contactor where the switch isn't closing fully. Even if nothing is physically blocking the fan, the motor may be vibrating so intensely that it creates the illusion of something being stuck inside. These electrical interferences are common when the unit is under strain, and they can escalate quickly into a fire hazard if left unattended. The safest and most effective solution is to have a technician replace the faulty capacitor or repair the motor contacts immediately.",
